    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are primed for a high-ceiling performance today, spearheaded by **Gunnar Henderson**, who anchors the slate with a team-high 83.29 efficiency score. Facing Wacha, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a potent combination of a 4.61 xERA matchup, an leadoff spot, and favorable wind conditions that provide a 5% boost to his output. Following closely are **Kyle Tucker** (77.88) and **Jackson Merrill** (75.10); while **Kyle Tucker** battles a slightly unfavorable park factor against Mahle, his elite xwOBA of .372 keeps his floor high. Similarly, **Jackson Merrill** is a beneficiary of a significant +14% park adjustment, making him a primary target for counting stats as he looks to exploit the soft matchup against Sugano.\n\nPlatoon advantages are central to today\u2019s strategy, most notably for **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** and **Brady House**. Both are positioned to capitalize on a favorable matchup against Fuentes, whose 5.07 xERA allows for an aggressive stacking approach. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** earns a massive 19% boost from the SP skill differential, making him a top-tier play at 74.56. Conversely, we are navigating a difficult matchup for **Jacob Wilson**, who draws the elite arm of Gilbert; with a sub-40 score potential looming due to the SP\u2019s 2.86 xERA, **Jacob Wilson** remains the most volatile start in our active lineup.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was **Marcell Ozuna**, who narrowly missed the cut with a 60.82 score. While **Marcell Ozuna** carries strong potential against Leiter, he was edged out by the superior projected efficiencies of our active OF and UTIL group. We are currently holding our breath on several \"Lineup Pending\" statuses for **Miguel Vargas**, **Jackson Merrill**, **Kyle Tucker**, and **Andy Pages**. Should those official lineups shift these players down in the order, their efficiency scores will need to be re-evaluated immediately to ensure we aren't wasting game caps on suboptimal spots.",
